        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName><hi rend="print">Down, | Beckenham, Kent.</hi></placeName>
                    <date>Dec. 28. 75</date>
                    <salute>My dear Wallace</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>I am very glad that you will attend, as it seems to me an occasion when every man of Science should help another. You will be able to return at night, as Lankester will be the first man ballotted for.<ref target="#foot.f1"/> I hope you are getting nearly to the end of your work</p>
<p>Yrs very sincerely | Ch. Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

            
            
            
            
        </div>

        

        

        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">CD had asked Wallace to attend a meeting of the <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_2944.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Linnean Society</ref> on 3 February 1876 in order to support <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_2814.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Edwin Ray Lankester’s</ref> second attempt to be elected a fellow of the society (see <ref target="./DCP-LETT-10322.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter to A. R. Wallace, 23 December 1875</ref>). Wallace’s letter has not been found.</note>
        </div>        
            
